# Notable Snippets

p.5

The only way to learn a new programming language is by writing programs in it.
The first program to write is the same for all languages. The first program to
write is the same for all languages:

  Print the words hello, world

This is the big hurdle; to leap over it you have to be able to create the
program text somewhere, compile it successfully, load it, run it, and find out
where your output went. With these mechanical details mastered, everything else
is comparatively easy.

